<br>
The process takes a couple of hours. There will most likely be a few applicants that will be taking their tests. Chuck will have some help from other master casting instructors from around the country to do the testing. Generally he gives alot of his time to help out the Federation to test at the Sow Bug and the Conclave. You might be the only guy from Arkansas but there may be others from Texas, Missouri, Louisana, etc.<br>
<br>
I'll be happy to sit and work with you prior to the test if you like. You are an excellent caster no doubt. You are one of the best casters I've seen so you should have no trouble. I can point you to all the things I &quot;didn't&quot; know prior to getting prepared for the test. By getting prepared for testing you'll be suprised at all the things you'll learn. There are so many little &quot;facts&quot; that will make every thing easier once you know them you'd be amazed. <br>
<br>
Chuck is also an excellent teacher and will be terrific to test with. I'll have to relay my testing experience with you one of these days. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'll be on the river for several days for the next couple of weeks. Let me know when you want to get together and we'll go over some of what I didn't know prior to the test.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chuckeasterling>chuck easterling</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Casting Corner Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(2/21/03 1:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> certified casting instruction question</span><hr size=1> Good afternoon Andrew,<br>
<br>
I would suggest that you pick-up a copy of Bill Gammel's &quot;The Essentials of Casting&quot; ($2.00 from FFF) a copy of Mel Krieger's &quot;Observations on Teaching Casting&quot; ($1.00 from FFF) and a copy of Gary Borger's video tape &quot;15 Most Common Casting Errors.&quot;  (FFF about $10.00)<br>
<br>
There are several other good books and videos.<br>
<br>
I know you are a good caster, but as John has indicated, a fair amount of the test involves teaching concepts and the above and other works will help you with that aspect of the test.  By all means take time to talk with John as it helps a great deal to talk with some one who has taken the test and did quite well.<br>
<br>
                                  Chuck   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=holland@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Holland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(2/21/03 8:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Certified casting instructor question</span><hr size=1> Is it too late to sign up?  This is something I've considered doing for several years, but never gotten around to.  Not something I wanted to &quot;show off&quot;, it's just that I've helped many people over the years improve their cast and I thought going through the certification process would make ME feel more comfortable.  Maybe I need to come and watch!<br>
